// Main API Route Handler
// The central HTTP API for the server. Handles all /api/* routes: sessions, projects,
// diagrams, designs, documents, spreadsheets, snippets, lessons, todos, metadata,
// terminal sessions, question/UI interactions, and health. All session-scoped routes
// create fresh per-request managers tied to the project+session path.

A scratch session at ~/.mermaid-collab/scratch is registered on startup.
Managers (DiagramManager, DocumentManager, etc.) are created fresh per request for the
relevant project+session — not shared across requests.
serverStartTime is recorded at module load for uptime calculation.

---

FUNCTION expandPath(path) -> string
  If path starts with ~/, replace ~ with the home directory.
  Return the expanded path.

---

FUNCTION getSessionParams(url) -> { project, session } | null
  Extract project and session from URL query params.
  IF either is missing, return null.

---

FUNCTION handleHealthCheck(wsHandler) -> Response
  CALLS: getConnectionCount (handler)
  Compute uptime from serverStartTime.
  Check if ui/dist/index.html exists to determine UI status.
  Return JSON with healthy (api && ui), services (api port, ui running, ws connection count), pid, and uptime string.

---

FUNCTION createManagers(project, session) -> managers
  CALLS: resolvePath (session-registry), DiagramManager (diagram-manager), DocumentManager (document-manager), SpreadsheetManager (spreadsheet-manager), SnippetManager (snippet-manager), MetadataManager (metadata-manager)
  Resolve all subdirectory paths (diagrams, documents, spreadsheets, snippets) via sessionRegistry.
  Instantiate and initialize all five managers.
  Return them as a bundle.

---

FUNCTION handleAPI(req, _diagramManager, _documentManager, _metadataManager, validator, renderer, wsHandler) -> Response    EXPORT
  CALLS: handleHealthCheck, createManagers, archiveSession (collab-state), addLesson (lessons), listLessons (lessons), listTodos (todos), addTodo (todos), removeTodo (todos), updateTodo (todos), listDesignsHandler (design-routes), createDesignHandler (design-routes), getDesignHandler (design-routes), updateDesignHandler (design-routes), parseTaskGraph (task-sync), buildBatches (task-sync), getDisplayName (state-machine)
  The per-request managers passed in are unused — fresh ones are created via createManagers.
  Routes are matched by path and method in order:

  SESSION REGISTRY (/api/sessions):
    GET: List all registered sessions (no-cache).
    POST: Register project+session (expand ~ first). IF newly created, broadcast session_created.
    DELETE: Unregister a session.
    POST /api/sessions/archive: Archive the session directory. IF deleteSession=true, unregister and broadcast session_deleted.

  PROJECT REGISTRY (/api/projects):
    GET: List all registered projects (no-cache).
    POST: Register a new project. Path must be absolute and must exist on disk. Return 201 with project details.
    DELETE: Unregister a project by path query param.

  HEALTH: GET /api/health delegates to handleHealthCheck.

  SESSION STATE: GET /api/session-state — read collab-state.json from the session directory (checks new path first, then old path for backwards compatibility). Augment with displayName if missing.

  TASK GRAPH: GET /api/projects/:project/sessions/:session/task-graph
    IF session state has batches, build a Mermaid graph TD from those batches with per-task status colors (pending=muted gray, in_progress=muted blue, completed=muted green, failed=muted red).
    ELSE fall back to parsing task-graph.md via parseTaskGraph/buildBatches, coloring nodes by wave index.
    Return { diagram, batches, completedTasks, pendingTasks }.

  UI STATE: GET /api/ui-state — return the cached UI object for the session key, or { status: 'none' } if absent.

  STATUS: GET /api/status — return current agent status from statusManager.

  DIAGRAMS (session-scoped, all broadcast changes via wsHandler):
    GET /api/diagrams: list all diagrams.
    GET /api/diagram/:id/history: return update log history (original + changes). Empty { original: null, changes: [] } if no history yet.
    GET /api/diagram/:id/version?timestamp=: replay update log to a specific timestamp.
    GET /api/diagram/:id: fetch a single diagram. 404 if not found.
    POST /api/diagram (create): validate content first. Register session if needed. Create diagram, broadcast diagram_created.
    POST /api/diagram/:id (update): validate content first. Save, log the update, broadcast diagram_history_updated (if changeCount > 0) and diagram_updated.
    DELETE /api/diagram/:id: delete and broadcast diagram_deleted.

  DESIGNS (session-scoped, delegate file I/O to design-routes handlers via mock req/res):
    GET /api/designs: list all designs.
    POST /api/design (create): register session, delegate to createDesignHandler, broadcast design_created.
    GET /api/design/:id/history: return update log history.
    GET /api/design/:id/version?timestamp=: replay to timestamp.
    GET /api/design/:id: delegate to getDesignHandler.
    POST /api/design/:id (update): delegate to updateDesignHandler, log update, broadcast design_history_updated and design_updated.
    DELETE /api/design/:id: delete file directly, broadcast design_deleted.
    POST /api/design/:id/export: broadcast design_export_request to browser via WebSocket, await browser upload (15s timeout). Return image binary or 408 on timeout.
    POST /api/design-export-result/:requestId: receive rendered image from browser, resolve the pending export promise.

  RENDER/VALIDATE/TRANSPILE (no session mutation):
    GET /api/render/:id: fetch diagram, render to SVG, return with Content-Type: image/svg+xml.
    GET /api/thumbnail/:id: fetch diagram, generate thumbnail SVG.
    POST /api/validate: validate Mermaid content, return { valid, error?, line? }.
    GET /api/transpile/:id: check diagram is SMACH YAML, transpile to Mermaid, return { mermaid }.

  DOCUMENTS (session-scoped, same pattern as diagrams with history/version/create/update/delete/broadcast):
    Includes GET /api/document/:id/clean for clean content without formatting.

  SPREADSHEETS (session-scoped, same CRUD+history pattern).

  SNIPPETS (session-scoped, same CRUD+history pattern):
    POST and PUT /api/snippet/:id both update (POST is deprecated).
    POST /api/snippet/:id/apply: read snippet JSON, extract filePath and code. IF startLine/endLine present, splice lines into the target file. ELSE overwrite the file entirely.

  LESSONS:
    GET /api/lessons: list all lessons for session.
    POST /api/lesson: register session, add lesson, broadcast lesson_added.

  TODOS (project-scoped, no session required):
    GET /api/todos: list todos for project.
    POST /api/todos: create todo (auto-creates a vibe session), register that session, optionally create a description document in it. Return 201.
    PATCH /api/todos/:id: update todo title.
    DELETE /api/todos/:id: remove todo.

  METADATA:
    GET /api/metadata: return full metadata object for session.
    POST /api/metadata/item/:id: update item folder/locked status, broadcast metadata_updated.
    POST /api/metadata/folders: create, rename, or delete a folder, broadcast metadata_updated with foldersChanged=true.

  QUESTION/UI:
    GET /api/question: return current pending question for session key.
    POST /api/question-response: resolve the pending question with a response, broadcast question_responded.
    POST /api/dismiss-ui: dismiss current question, broadcast ui_dismissed.
    POST /api/update-ui: broadcast ui_updated with patch payload.
    POST /api/render-ui: generate a uiId, broadcast ui_render. IF blocking=false, cache via uiManager and return immediately. IF blocking (default), await uiManager.renderUI response.
    GET /api/ui-response: poll for UI response status by uiId.
    POST /api/ui-response: receive UI response from browser, forward to uiManager.

  TERMINAL SESSIONS (PTY-backed):
    POST /api/terminal/sessions: create PTY session via ptyManager, persist session record via terminalManager. Return { id, tmuxSession, wsUrl } with 201.
    GET /api/terminal/sessions: list sessions sorted by order, augmented with live alive status from ptyManager.
    DELETE /api/terminal/sessions/:id: kill PTY, remove from persisted sessions, recompute order. Return 204.
    POST /api/terminal/sessions/:id/rename: update session name in persisted storage.
    PUT /api/terminal/sessions/reorder: validate orderedIds covers all sessions exactly once, reorder array and update order fields.

  Unmatched routes return 404.
